this verbal jumble was the key to the recollection which excited and disturbed professor angell .
he questioned the sculptor with scientific minuteness ; and studied with frantic intensity the on which the youth had found himself working , chilled and clad only in his night clothes , when waking had stolen bewilderingly over him .
my uncle blamed his old age , wilcox afterwards said , for his slowness in recognizing both hieroglyphics and pictorial design .
